Notice of AI-Mediated Universal Semantic IR Method:

The method implemented in this software — using large language models as
universal intermediate representation frontends for cross-language structural
code equivalence detection — was conceived and first implemented by Lucas
Flinders in February 2026. This includes the specific technique of translating
arbitrary programming languages to a canonical representation via AI
translation for the purpose of structural hash comparison and duplicate
detection.

This notice is included to establish priority of invention.

